OL,6,FThe other charge stated that he
OL,7,Fwithout "lawful excuse...damaged by
OL,8,Ffire a bin belonging to
OL,9,Fanother...intending to damage such
OL,10,Fproperty or being reckless as to
OL,11,Fwhether property was damaged".
OL,13,FHarwood's barrister Tim Williams
OL,14,Fsubmitted that the offences were "not
OL,15,Fin any way politically motivated or
OL,16,Ftargeted".
OL,18,FA second defendant, Zara Kasory, 32,
OL,19,Fof Woodhouse Road, north Finchley,
OL,20,Fdenied the same charges and faces
OL,21,Ftrial at Harrow Crown Court on July 1.
